This is a strenuous 6-mile trail roundtrip. I suggest wearing hiking boots, bringing a knapsack of hydration, wearing a bathing suit under your clothing (nowhere to change) for the hot pool, wearing a cap and sunscreen,  and if you have a fear of heights to leave it at the trailhead.
On this hike, not only do you get to look at a waterfall. But you get to scramble on or around a waterfall to reach the ladder to the hot springs. How many hikes do you get to travel up a waterfall?

Here are the facts about Bonanza Trail: The westernmost point is at Angel Trail Park immediately northwest of Durango Drive at Summerlin Parkway. The easternmost point is where Bill Briare Family Park ends at the U.S. 95 fence. It is a 2.11 mile paved trail that connects to Charlie Kellogg & Joe Zaher Sports Complex, Lone Mountain Trail, and Kmart. Parking is at the Charlie Kellogg & Joe Zaher Sports Complex, Kmart, and Bill Bri are Family Park. It's parallel to Summerlin Parkway.

This is how to get to Shoreline Trail: From Lake Mead Parkway you proceed through the Fee Station into Lake Mead National Recreation Area where it changes to Lake Shore Drive. In a couple of miles you will turn left toward Las Vegas Bay. You keep stay on this road until it ends at the boat launch parking lot. The trail starts as a sidewalk to the right of the boat launch. At the bottom of the hill the trail will be on the right (bordered by rocks).
Shoreline Trail takes you to the spot where the Las Vegas Wash empties into Lake Mead.

The Thai chicken salad is also really amazing. My only suggestion is that they change the name of the soup to Peace Wonton Soup, not Wor.

Instead of wasting your time and money here, try sending your package from the UPS customer service center on 335 Arby Lane. It's not an independent UPS store, it's the actual UPS facility. You will save lots of money and have all shipping options available to you. These people on Green Valley are just greedy middle-men.
I love the Korean chicken. I get it skinless and prefer the healthier version. Very flavorful.
Try the sashimi salad for a healthy alternative. Good price, lots of food, and healthy.
The best cannoli I've ever had. The orange liqueur really adds a nice touch. Nothing compares to this!
Salmon tartare is amazing here! I also enjoyed the yellow tail with jalepeno.

A coffee & pastry here will cost you $6-$7 on average. The food here is generally good, but too expensive for what you get. I have no doubt that they use great ingredients, but so do a lot of places in this neighborhood for a lot less. Sprouts for example has the most amazing brewed coffee and muffins for just 99c each. You can also drive up the street to Whole Foods and get a coffee and pastry for $2.99 all day everyday, including vegan options.
Extremely dishonest dealership. I wouldn't be surprised if some of the positive reviews were fake.
Try the Apple Cobb Salad. Extremely good!
You can get a side of eggs for just $1.39. Get 2 or 3 and you have a relatively cheap meal at the airport
I've been to many locations. This is by far the best one!!!

My experience with Ryan Ray was not good. He promised me that my deposit was refundable and demanded I put down $1000 for an allocated car. I had every intention by buying the car, but it was gonna take a while to get since it was a new 2018. I decided not to get the car after 2 weeks, and I was told the deposit is not refundable. Ryan Ray lied to me. I wouldn't trust anything that comes out of this guy's mouth. Be very careful!

Don't ever leave a deposit here. It's not refundable. I wanted an allocated 2018 Crosstrek and they insisted I leave a $1000 deposit, which Ryan Ray assured me was refundable. Before the car arrived, I changed my mind. They refused to give me my $1000 deposit back. I had to raise hell to finally get it back. What a scam. Buyer beware!

The last time I used a credit card at this car wash, I got burned! I found nearly $200 of extra charges from Oasis. There were over fifty extra charges billed in different amounts ranging from $2-$6 and I was being billed on a daily basis. Although I was able to dispute all the excess charges with my credit card company, this didn't stop new charges from piling on a daily basis. I had to cancel my credit card just to prevent this glitch (or scam) from affecting me. Total headache!!!!!
When you can't decide what to get here, go for a Carne Asada Torta. The bread is pretty amazing. Great sandwich for a great price.
Just a tip, the men's restroom doesn't lock. This can lead to some funny moments. I told the manager about this and he just threw his hands in the air like he just didn't care. Good times.

Chocolate Veggiechino: amazing blend of flavors! Who would have thought to mix chocolate and coffee beans and avocado and kale\/collard greens\/spinach together. These ingredients sound like odd pairings, but I was pleasantly surprised by how wonderful (and addictive) this drink really is. A bit pricey at $7, but definitely worth it because it keeps you full. A perfect substitute for morning coffee and breakfast all in one. I always get mine with almond milk. You gotta try it!
Chaotic and disorganized. They lost my online order. I asked for a refund and felt like I had to beg. They need to clean up their act at this location.

#6 BBQ Pork is the best sandwich here. I recommend getting extra meat and extra veggies added for just a little more. Perfect sandwich for sharing. For something sweet, I love the taro smoothie with boba. Best I've had anywhere.
I like the white fish with garlic water sauce and cabbage as the starch option. It makes the meal healthy and delicious.
The sandwich shop in here is a hidden gem. I highly recommend the subs!
The zucchini banana bread with the chocolate chips is fantastic. Goes great with the wonderful coffee they serve. Friendly staff as well!
The review by Ryan M. is most certainly fake. He is a physician who has close ties to this pharmacy and has a family member who works there.

Don't bother asking them for a simple cup of tap water with your order. It will cost you $2 for that tap water, even if you and purchasing other items from them. Extremely disappointed in the service and attitude of the staff. It's as if they really don't want to be bothered by customers. Cool I can take a hint.
I love the Bullet Proof Monk Coffee. Wonderful mix of flavors with the grass fed butter and coconut oil. I also enjoyed the Dragon Fries. Very spicy and addictive, just how I like it.

I think this gym is fantastic. It's 5 times better than any other gym in Vegas. My only issue is that it's also 10 times more expensive than any other gym in Vegas. Not worth the expense if you ask me, but still a wonderful place. They raise prices with very little warning. It used to cost $10 a month to freeze your membership, now it's $30 a month. Easy call to cancel.

I ordered the chicken shawarma and paid $6.99 (regular menu price). After paying, I noticed that the chicken shawarma was the daily special and should have been only $3.99. When I asked the owner about this, he said that $3.99 was for "fried chicken". I didn't see fried chicken on the menu. There was a picture of the chicken shawarma with $3.99 clearly displayed next to it. Also outside the sign advertised chicken shawarma for $3.99. Very dishonest. There is no difference between special & menu.

The service here is by far the best of any sushi restaurant I've been to. The sushi is very good and they bring a lot of unique elements that I haven't seen anywhere else. I recommend trying the Black Lemon Roll. Made with black rice. Fantastic!

I'm happy that they carry the Monq portable aromatherapy diffusers here! It's a very unique product and I am happy with my purchase. They will let you sample them before you buy. I personally like the Active and Healthy.
Chinese fast food! Excellent fried rice. Boboa teas were too sweet..
Quick and very friendly service !

My 5-year old loves this place! Definitely worth the admission price. Average visit for us is 2 hours.  If my son had his way, we'd be there till closing. Staff is awesome too-- friendly and interact with the kids. There's a snack center with vending machines but we usually bring our own snacks :-) which is not prohibited.
I have their chicken fried rice at least once a week!
Gyro and Feta Fries are unbelievable!!  One of my favorite places in Las Vegas.
Very great pizza, crust is the best part and very crunchy. Best pizza around.

It's important to give your pharmacist time to fill your prescription. Rush the pharmacist and there could be dire consequences! Narcotic prescriptions always, always take longer to fill. And even though, you may only be filling something that does not need to be counted, i.e. birth control or inhaler, you may be the 10th person in line or there could be issues with insurance that bumps the wait time up. It's never "just put it in the bag." 

NEVER RUSH YOUR PHARMACIST EVER!!!

Food was really good! The stand outs were the truffle mac cheese and the potatoes and mushroom on the truffle chicken . Very unimpressed by the slow and unattentive service, esp for such a classy place
Super good jerky! triple threat is hot but not burning your mouth hot. Good texture & flavor. Up to par with our other fave, Cecina jerky from suns beef jerky

Better than steak n shake! Decent steakburgers & chocolate Brownie concrete. But not better and actually,pricier than in n out. Avr meal for a couple can run you $17~20 vs $12 at in & out.Food came out fast & good service. None of my family members were impressed
Got the red velvet malasada with chocolate, macadamia nut and chantilly filling. Total of 5 malasadas and Hawaiian sun for $9 and change
Free wifi!

Called you guys multiple times today ,  even went to this address and can't find the location at the shopping center!! U lost my business coz another pest control place answered their phones right away
Food was ok. Our party still prefers lucilles. Highlight was the strawberry jello cake in the mason jar. Wings are better at Gritz Cafe.
Chocolate peanut butter with vanilla gelati is amazeballs!! Great staff, definitely sample everything! Bf likes the Swedish fish
Wings are pretty big, wish it were crispier but good Jameson sauce!
Calamari w\/ sauce is pretty good. I thought crown and anchors pot pies were much better though. Unlv rebel bar! Lots of tvs to support our team
Bacon temptation omelette. They got red velvet pancakes! Excellent service by Jose
Full groom $29

Bf got the wings & I got boneless! Got the mnf special. We were very happy with our food and service. Big fan of the chili lime sauce! The fries were great. We got the sweet chili fries but probably gonna try the regular flavor next time coz we can tell these are bomb plain!!
Red velvet microwaved for 15 to 30 secs.....redonkulous!! The texture of the  cake with the melted chocolate was a big thumbs up
Bf prefers H&H's ribs better (according to Vegas standards). He's very picky, esp since we've gone to the rib cook off lol
Bun bo hue had gr8 flavors but way too much pork fat,  not enough meat. Really good pho tai & excellent service (we had a male server,  not the short lady ppl rant about)
Oreo & peanut butter stuffed cookies were good. Red velvet lacked flavor and the vanilla with rolo barely had enough rolos in the middle for me to taste the stuffing.

Had faux wood & vertical blinds done in my entire house. It took 1.5 wks from initial consultation to get them installed & about 2 hrs for the work to be completed. Thx to owner Patricia for suggesting faux wood & the colors for the blinds. It really complemented our place!
Just called them right now and the host said they are open Fri and Saturday nights starting 10pm....look forward to checking them out!!
Wish more ppl knew about this spot. Laid back, good music, great service by owner, Jeff! Limited liquor & no drink menu though. they are planning to do a Latin night on Fridays!

I can barely taste the difference btwn Guthries & Canes but all I know is that it's not worth the drive when i've got canes down the st from my house. Great customer service! Skip the slaw & get double toast!
Linked with kmart so don't forget to give them your number for the shop your way rewards points
Gr8 service from the gentleman at the watch repair\/battery section (next to optical). He's closed on Sundays. He changed the batteries for 7 watches in under 1.5 hrs

If you have a large party, try to get the private dining room. So gorgeous with fresh flowers on the table for display. They will tack on 20% gratuity for a big group. A beautiful restaurant. Food is ok, but for the $, lindo michoacan & tacos el gordo all the way!
Huge pieces of shrimp. I prefer my sisig slightly crispy, but my bf had no issue with it. He liked the peppers and seasoning. My fries were undercooked. Friendly service
So rumor has it that California crab is closing down and Hot N Juicy bought it out and taking over!!

I enjoyed the porchetta but not so much of the fried chicken. Was not a fan of the overpowering rosemary taste.  Liked how juicy and meaty it was though. Wish they would create fried chicken that tasted like Gritz Cafe! Now that's bomb chicken

Excellent service! Chicken & waffles is really good, close second to gritz cafe. Open till 9pm, so I can get my chic\/waff fix for dinner since Gritz closes at 3pm. they serve you complementary corn bread as an app
Bf and I were more impressed with their fusion tacos than the ever popular Komex
Tantan ramen ftw!
Don't leave until you try the bananas foster gourmet ice cream sandwich. My bf, who hates bananas, even loves it!! We had pretty good & attentive service today
They are opening one in Henderson (Stephanie st) by the end of April 2014
Biloxi fried chicken is overhyped! Tastes like something I can get at any bar
Slurpee,  smoothie, soda and tea station... And inexpensive donuts!!

Disappointed with the options this year. For the price we're paying for food, its silly to even charge admission. Best stuff we've tried were fist of fusions Notorious rib\/ kalua pork tacos and bens bbq brisket
White castle was organized alot smoother this yr. More lines, even a separate truck for small slider orders. No more 2.5 hr wait!
The Yelp $15 dollar deal is not valid on single taco purchases.  Must be an entrée. $2 tacos.  Fiancé enjoyed the carnitas.  They have nothing on El Gordos adobada tho!
Called for an inquiry & left vm, claiming to return calls within 10 mins. It's been 24 hrs & nada....
The place to be for EDM lovers! Be prepared to pay $18 for a simple drink
They got a speakeasy room to the left of the main bar where you have to get a time slot for the guestlist.  specialty cocktails there! They are actually a separate entity from commonwealth

Great crispy Napoleon. Couldn't taste the condensed milk on the Bird roll, honey cake was too sweet & buttery. Russian cake was meh...not really digging the fruit infused with the cake. Lots of macarons!
Not as good as Monta, jinya or fukumimi ramen.
Chocolate satin pie!! Not overly sweet with an amazing cookie crust
Nyki did an amazing job spraying me for my wedding. No orange and I looked like I spent a week at the islands
They charge $4 to sew in one coat button! :-0 my pant hem (not jeans)  were $6. Friendly staff but English is limited

Spacious, dark room with bright blue neon lights. Excellent service from the bartenders. Was here for their May the 4th be with you event & they had star wars playing on every tv in addt to specialty star wars cocktails.
Gingerbread frap was ok in flavor but ur better off getting the latte version! Egg nog latte is also avail for the holidays too!

Brisket sandwich was good & ribs were pretty meaty. Careful with their hot bbq sauce coz its really hot! Not the best in lv tho. Staff: stop asking ur customers to vote for best bbq. One reminder was good enuff, but mult times is ridiculous.

The fat Elvis was sooooo yummy! The banana\/pb filling was delicious and the chocolate icing wasnt overly sweet. My bf really enjoyed the maple bacon donut. Can't wait to try the tiramisu\/coffee & salted caramel donut!
They are opening a location at town square next to the MAC cosmetics store!!! (formerly Bonn bread)
Another location opening in Henderson! (eastern\/siena heights) by the chipotle!
Opens at 11am...closes as late as 2am on the weekend. Excellent service from Alex. Rec farm burger and truffle fries. Home made ketchup is bomb!
They are opening one in Henderson (Stephanie st) by the end of April 2014
Tacos El Gordo is still the best but this is def up there. We got the steak tacos and it's way better than Taco Taco. The medium salsa def had a kick!

Great spot to watch sports for Chicago fans! Good deep dish, esp enjoyed the crust. Expect a half hr wait for them to make it. Select alcoholic beverages available. Can't wait to try the chocolate covered cheesecake on a stick!
Hrs on yelp are wrong. Host says they are closed at 11pm
Had bottle service here and the servers for our table were so stunning, friendly, attentive! Great experience, and very pleased with the staff. Awesome music and cool pole dancing act
Nightclub already closed. Steakhouse remains open
Clean establishment, service slower than el gordo, was more impressed with the asada & al pastor from el gordo. Good corn on the cob though. Tacorron (with chicharron) was ok
Happy hour all day Sunday! Closed Monday. Happy hr from 5 to 9pm on other days! $3-4 hh apps. Unlv bar! Tons of tvs for sports fans!!
I'm the minority and although I only had the pepperoni, I was more impressed with my food than secret pizza. My bf agrees as well
Total Wine has a better set up and bigger selection of booze
Get your maps & take your potty break here before proceeding
The food here is good but I prefer Yalla more. The chicken here is dry imho. Yallas has an awesome citrus flavor & their rice is better

Nice decor! Gave the atmosphere a sensual vibe. Phone chargers @ the bar but I think it only works for iphones. Raunchy names for drinks! We've only had the edamame to eat but it was spot on. Thumbs up on the specialty drinks too

No fun games & great prizes at 1221on a Friday night like the banner claimed & the waiter had no clue what I was talking about. Friendly service! Spicy Bulgogi beef was way too saucy, u def need some rice to mix w\/this. Nice place for kpop lovers! Cool music
Jonas did a superb job w\/our engagement photos & video montage. His prices are awesome for the quality of work! He can also customize your save the dates!

Pretty good lemon pepper & garlic parmesan boneless wings! Very impressed with our service & friendly staff that acknowledged us. Wish they would put a giant tv screen among the other little ones, but a pretty good spot for sport fans to hang. Hope they'll have a full liquor license soon
They've got tons of the new coke machine that you can mix up different flavors now!! The liquor bar is to your left when you walk in

The tilapia w\/ scallops & shrimp was seasoned well n pretty tasty! Bang bang shrimp was good but not hype worthy. Thumbs up on the watermelon martini. Corn chowder was meh. Was pleased w\/ our service!
Huge fan of their rice crispy treats! Right amount of sweetness, airy like chew to it. Kitchen sink is very good too, esp if u are an oreo fan

5 star reviews from yelpers with zero to five friends , including out of towners????? 2 of which r u, June D.This place MUST be legit!!! Find it odd to stay in a hotel yet manage to eat at a brand spankin new restaurant off the strip...waay in Henderson
Combo fajitas for 2 is so much food! It's seriously enough to feed 3 ppl. Try their homemade sauces!
I found tons of Jeans that are popular (levis, blue asphalt, etc) for under $5!!! They got lots of cute shirts for a couple of bucks that would be good as lounge wear or for the gym

Sorry, but I have to pick marquee over hakka. They both have multiple floors w\/ different music, but this place is too hyped up. Went to watch Calvin Harris, the crowd was insane & i felt like a smooshed sardine
Love the recliner seats! The button is on the right side between the seat and arm rest in case you can't find it in the dark lol
Only dentist in town that performs laser frenectomy! My daughter had a tongue tie & she's significantly less gassy & is eating more!
Highly recommend their orange dreamsicle flavor!!

Really disappointed w\/ the service @ foodie fest. Took over 30+ minutes @ the PICK UP line for shaved ice, missed the jabbawockeez performance since I was stuck waiting, they forgot to add the condensed milk & gave me the wrong flavor!!! (I asked for almond, not lemonade)
Tacos naut was very good but all I tasted was wonton, rice and sauce. Didn't taste any salmon. Looking forward to trying more stuff from this truck!
Great instructor,  puts beginners at ease. Was scared to paint for the first time and she did a great job explaining step by step. Totally happy with the outcome. They do private parties!
Garlic edamame is a must
Smokehouse beef &  cheddar brisket is soooooo noms
Got an order to go,  didn't double check my bag & they forgot my pita bread that ppl rave about !! Chicken kabobs were crazy good. Has a nice citrus taste
No hurricanes , only beer, and expect to wait almost 1.5 to two hrs to get crawfish! Limited vendors. The highlight was the pineapple yogurt drink

Such a beautiful spot! Love the backyard garden & figurines of birds humping each other. Reasonably priced drinks! Pillow talk was very good. Unicorn had a very prominent ginger taste w\/ a bit of tartness, but wasn't bad either
The art bar was very chic, the decor of the lobby & restaurants r def more modern\/classy. By far the best looking interior for a DT hotel ! Def try pizza rock ;-)
Excellent pork belly bowl!! Wasn't impressed by my ramen. We still prefer the broth\/flavor at fukumumi ramen. Friendly staff tho

They really pack on the meat! My 2nd fave, right behind viva las arepas. Highly recommend putting some of the hot sauce or green sauce on your food! Really enjoyed the shredded beef n bf loved the pork
Soooo many beautiful things for home decor. I felt like I was at a Pottery Barn. Uber cute accessories. This store is quite large & a great spot for girly girls or if you love decorating!
Sign up for their club card so you can return or exchange items in case you lose your receipt

I usually go to El Gordo for tacos but they have really good ones here as well.  I still vote El Gordo at having better adobada but tijuana is definitely up there too.  They really pack on the meat w\/their asada
Really enjoyed their sisig! Crispy with a good spice to it. Rec putting a bit of vinegar on it too.  Clean facility. $7.99 Filipino ayce in Henderson!
Definitely try the lobster balls!

Two voicemails and an email  and still no communication,  Viva?? Guess you just lost a customer. And apparently,  if u bought a Groupon,  one hr of the total hrs u paid for will be for set up & take down. No thank u!
They also serve cjs Italian ice here!! Thoroughly enjoyed my cheesesteak, esp with the soft roll! Friendly service!!
They don't sell comic books here. Under new ownership

Cool specialty cocktails. I enjoyed my Eros which had a prominent ginger beer flavor (bf said it tasted like a Moscow mule) & my bf enjoyed his  Crucifix drink that contained absinthe. Great service from the bartenders! Look for the neon blue bunny sign outside!
Thank u Dr. Ruess,  Joan the RN & Margaret at ultrasound for being so kind,  through & never making me feel rushed. I would have never known how bad my veins r if it wasn't for your team
Very similar to China a go go even though I think China a go go is better of the two (esp the one on windmill). Cheap lunch specials! Kung pao & mangolian beef weren't bad at all!
Here at 3pm on a Saturday 6\/8\/13, yelp says it's open at noon. Place is locked up and no one is picking up their phone. No sign posted about whereabouts. Waste of gas!!!
Just got a voicemail. Frost bites closed today 6\/8\/13. Wish they would post on yelp about days they are closing coz it was a journey to get here!!! Gas is expensive, ppl!!!

A lighter, airy-er, texture than ice cream. All natural, made with less than 5 ingredients. I've only tried the black sesame, which they toasted themselves. Def a healthier alternative to reg ice cream. Fresh fruit avail for toppings but my heifer butt needs oreos & condensed milk to be happy lol

2 burgers\/sandwich w\/ fries & 2 drinks will set u back $20. Its def not Bachi burger but it wasn't bad. I would dine there if I was in the area, but it's not something I would go for automatically. Thumbs up on the unswt iced tea. Has a hint of mango??!!

Thank you,  Russell, for the gr8 customer service.  An oil service from that shady Purrfect Auto would have cost me almost $10 more if I was dumb enuff to go w\/them.  GY has a $20 oil special but was charged $17 for my Yelp check in
Amazing dancers & acrobats! There's really no bad seats at this theater! (sat at the lower level near aisle but the upper one still looks good!) No photos allowed during the show
My phatty philly was on the bland side & Bachis truffle fries were better, imho. My bfs cow bowl was pretty flavorful tho! Can't wait to try the drunken monkey cake next time!
I love low key burger joints & this did not disappoint. The fries are tasty & good for 2 ppl!! try ordering your burger with egg!
Easily my new fave spot downtown! Spacious, inviting, beautifully decorated, great music, lots of places to sit, free games. Love the giant jenga at the outside patio area
Total b*tc# splitting checks for a party of 20 ppl (esp w\/ numerous tapas). Prepare for a headache!
Corned beef hash, potatoes & banana muffin r on point. Big portions
Thai monster bowl was good & fiancé approves of the bison burger. Thumbs down on swt potato fries. Excited to try their frozen yogurt & snickers coffee next time !

Seth took his time to color, cut & deep condition my hair. Even with a haircut, he managed to keep it long! Looked very shiny afterwards & was kind enuff to curl my hair. Friendly & gave me hair tips!  He's my new go to hair person!!!
Caramel hazelnut latte is amazeballs! Red velvet latte was ok but next time, ill try the red velvet hot cocoa
Good variety of spices and tea,  but we enjoy the OO at Totally Olive more
Reminiscent of the Cadillac Ranch days, minus the mechanical bull. Only positives are the cheap drinks and good music
They've got 2 HHs daily at the bar area and it only applies to booze.. 30% off. Beautiful decor. Sauce on grilled wings was good but not a fan of texture

Went on a Rock Shot Bingo event (check calendar on website) . They gave away free cupcakes & jello shots. Great music,  younger crowd than I expected & no need to stamp coz everything is done electronically. Had a blast!
Don't be dumb like me and bit half of a spicy green pepper from the Molcajete familiar. Could not eat my food for over 10 mins coz it was burniiiiiing
Highly rec the Cal Italia pizza! The Boss has 12 toppings, awesome crust & frikken huge! Bf loved their specially cocktails. Great service from bartender, David!
Excellent service from bartender,  Saul! Really enjoyed my nuts &  berries drink. Fiancé loved his Aviation.  Sweet bowling area.  Def gonna sample the food next time
You can get your sandwich wrapped in lettuce if you don't want to eat bread called "unwich" . Still prefer port of subs
They've got mini honey toast for dessert. Great sushi and they allow half rolls.  Amazing service & my picky fiancé approves

Bland\/poor quality food. Tastes like it was microwaved. Doesn't even come close to Firefly. If u want cheap, bar tapas, I highly recommend Remixx. Service is friendly, but slow. Bf had to go up to server to finally get our check
Pretty impressed w\/their effiency. In & out in half an hr for an ultrasound. Staff is very friendly. Let's just hope nothing in billing gets screwed! (looking at the neg reviews)
Gr8 kalua pig! Bf likes the guava habanero sauce. Guess they are planning to open another location in the Green Valley\/Henderson area!
Pretty good beef tamales. My bf liked the chicken as well but I thought it was bland. Make sure you put some of their hot green sauce on top!!! Gr8 customer service. Will be back to try their tacos
Largest variety and best priced quest bars i've seen in a nutrition store
Excellent service from technician, Carlton! One of the most pleasant people and very helpful man. Great eye contact, always smiling, and nice enough to wear booties in our house

Gr8 service from our waitress,  extremely slow to come out with our entrées (waited over 30 mins for a nonbusy day). Pb & j burger was good but they add an insane amt of lettuce. Take it off & the burger doesn't seem as huge as presented.
Better than settebello imho. Gr8 service from Chef Marc who showed us the ropes. Pizza done in 90 secs. Each pie is one size, bf & i ended up eating 2 to satisfy us
Daily happy hour at tavern area from 10p till 4a! Highly rec mini kobe sliders with the crispy fries dipped in aoli sauce!! Awesome service from graveyard bartender
Located inside Albertsons

Amazing service from Cindy! Rib eye was excellent and so was the grilled octopus. Don't leave without trying the turtle sundae! They have brunch on Saturdays and Sundays! Can we say bottomless Mimosas?
Thumbs up on the carne asada burrito. If u decide to get the shredded beef,  highly suggest getting it smothered w\/the green sauce. Friendly service (cute,  high school girl. Don't know her name)
Krissy is very down to earth! She did a beautiful job with my cut & color (used Schwarzkopf color). She did a great blowout after & gave me nice Kim K waves. U can find her at Divine Salon.
2 levels of awesomeness. They have great suits\/jackets for guys & the latest trend in fashion for women. Prices are affordable! Store is clean & better stocked... but not as large as the one at TS.

Huge tenders! It comes w\/ fries  & it could've been an entree from the amt ur getting. Chicken roulade with mashed potatoes had gr8 flavor! classy looking ambience. Bleu cheese burger gets a huge thumbs up!

Gluten free & organic options! They are planning to serve gluten free desserts. Great service from bartender, Nate. Check out the coasters w\/ questions printed on them. Nice icebreaker for a date! Lol
The Hercules is a must have for peanut butter lovers!
They are opening a location at town square next to the MAC cosmetics store!!! (formerly Bonn bread)
Another location opening in Henderson! (eastern\/siena heights) by the chipotle!
Pistachio frappe is really good! Taste like a melted pistachio ice cream. My hubby enjoyed the toffee frappe
If all fails with the free parking sections ,  the garage charges $20 for parking.  Convenient and short walk to LIB
Really good bulgogi! I really enjoyed the sushi w\/peanut butter on it! They allow half rolls. They've got Korean ramen here too but skip that coz the noodles taste like those cheap instant ones
Sriracha flavored and bacon flavored candy canes for the holidays! Yummm

Food was good but was a little shocked when I ordered brisket sliders & on my plate were 2 of them (fairly small on Hawaiian roll) ,  no fries & it costing $12...looked @ other pix on Yelp & seeing 3 sliders per plate. Did they f#%$ me over??
Scenic drive is beautiful. If u missed your exit for the trail, you have to go through the entire long drive bcoz it's one way!
$0.10 per page if you want to print things. Cheaper than staples or office max
Tons of leashes, beds, toys, harness at an affordable price! Dogs are welcome to the store ;-)
Great taste but I think I still prefer dq blizzards, esp for oreo
Orange cow tastes like orange creamsicles!!! You guys have to try CJs. Their concrete is great too
Our version of The Grove (like the one in Cali but much smaller & no fountains). They check for IDs after 9pm. Big play area for kids! One of the most beautiful spots downtown
Tried their Carne asada & adobada. Bland \/mediocre. You're better off at tacos el gordo and it's cheaper there too. You can get Margaritas (overly swt) & Mexican coke here
HH 5 to 0630 pm and 9pm to closing (2am) daily. Really good food (we did the 2 for $55), but we still prefer Korean bbq (tofu hut), which is cheaper & ayce
They have rooftop seating!! They don't put the heaters up there though :-(
Still in the moving process and will open sometime in August 2014. And they will continue to sell their popular, Russian Honey Cake!! (formerly Tverskaya Russian Restaurant)
They got rid of the smoke shop next door and it's now extended to a kusina ni Lorraine ayce buffet for $8.99! lechon on the weekends

My hubby (not pinoy) walks in to the buffet side & asks if he can get food to go, the buffet lady made him pay in the express side (for the buffet amt $8.99),& buffet lady scoops his food herself on the buffet side. My hubby was confused coz he asked for TO GO , which they should have led him to the express side & charge him express prices instead of one entree & rice for a buffet price!! And he didn't even scoop it himself!
Only came here for their signature drinks but i'm def looking fwd to trying out the food! They've got gluten free, dairy free, vegan options!

Best vet in Vegas,  imho. He actually takes the time to talk to you & answers your questions. You won't feel rushed. Staff is the friendliest & seem happy to do their job. Keurig machine in front lobby & they actually offer you bottled water too!

Popped gourmet popcorn available! (choc is gr8 while sipping dtb) Def get the sampler. The El Heffe was my fave. ( jalapeno beer )They pride themselves incorporating local business in their menu (ie: popped & a few beers from local breweries)
Are u guys reading the rebuttal of mgr,  Patricia?? Extremely unprofessional!  Was gonna buy a Groupon,  but she obviously doesn't respect ppls opinions &  has to cuss customers out
Friendly staff ,  generous portions,  good amount of seating . Enjoyed my chicken and rice

They have poutine! My bf liked this one better than the gross Pinks Hot Dogs on the strip. It's overpriced hot dogs, but you're paying for the location. If you're downtown, check out Cheffinis for much less
Time on Yelp is wrong. Saturday closed at 8 pm. Thank goodness I called before we drove there for nothing
They don't sell king cake by the slice & need 24 hr notice if u want it. Skip the coleslaw & get double cajun fries

The wayfarer bar inside Inspire was a nice, low key bar that serves specialty cocktails, import beers & wine. The Presidente was super bitter, my bf couldn't even finish a quarter of it. They have an upstairs patio area!
Take the elevator to go to the rooftop for a beautiful view & great music. Specialty cocktails are not avail tho & u have to go down to the wayfarer bar for that
Reminds me of a Fat Tuesday but weaker liquor. Very cute place!(super girly looking) Non alcohol options available
Has an outdoor bar for drinks to go! Foozeball, beer pong, black jack and a bar all at the same space :-O connected to the quad & linq
Triple threat jerky all the way! Triple threat peanuts are hotter than the jerky. Give them your email so they can send you coupons
Pretty good specialty drinks but get ur butt to the upstairs patio for a more open space & great music (dj played Hip hop Saturday night) . The specialty drinks are not available at the rooftop tho
Thumbs up on the swt chili calamari. Looking fwd to try their "second happy hr", from 8 to 10pm ($9 menu)
Belly buns! Oxtail fried rice was pretty good too
They serve Chicago tamales here too
glad they heard my plea to open near the Henderson area! Lol.Sprecher orange & creme and Jersey  cream is the best here! they got bacon cotton candy too
Crab balls were very tasty. They don't do half rolls here. Gr8 ambience,  feels like I'm in Japan
Ferris wheel can hold up to 30 ppl & a bartender for each cubicle!
Highly recommend the Lions Tail cocktail for a refreshing bourbon based drink
Pretty good wings & fries. Will not order back door pizza again. They mix the pizza sauce with the cheese. I prefer the taste of sauce then cheese on top. It was bland,  imo.

Food was avrg. Great spot to watch sports! Reminds me of hooters w\/ girls wearing teeny outfits. If you're looking for good bar eats, i rec yard house, but for a chill spot to watch sports and have drinks, give this place a try! Friendly service. $.50 charge for extra sauce :-(
The restaurant has 2 floors & u can get drinks to go! 2nd floor has keg room & outdoor patio. Amazing service from our Hawaiian server, Jonathan!  Very impressed w\/ the friendliness of all the staff
I'm usually a regular at Homegoods & this is definitely going to be on my route! Affordable and beautiful home decor. Lots of full length mirrors and a variety of clocks!
Thumbs up on tuna app & BP burger! Good signature drinks. Bartender told us they change it every season. Chic decor and gr8 service
I just spoke to a worker Today (tony) and he said they will be open for 24 hrs for the rest of the week! Located next to MAC cosmetics

They have the same phone # on the lake mead as the town square location yelp page so be specific when mentioning which location coz they gave me the wrong info! (I figured the town square location won't be open for 24 hrs when the worker mentioned that!). Located next to MAC cosmetics
Another location opening in Henderson! (eastern\/siena heights) by the chipotle!
Nice outdoor patio with beautiful bistro lighting and fireplace! Food was ur avrg bar food. Really enjoyed the cinnamon apple whiskey shot
This venue is pretty spacious!  Multiple bars! Telescope on outside patio area
Perk Me Up is a must have for coffee\/chocolate lovers! It comes with a yummy chocolate wafer too. Cool ambience! They have a drink with absinthe too
I've had pretty good experiences with the technician but I do agree their numbing cream sux! Waste of $20. Their laser hair removal machine is painful despite the cream
Cap'n crunch ice cream!!! Love the concept of cupcake and ice cream in the same cup!

Friendly service. Good burger (A1 *ran out of bacon*...gave it 3 stars), gr8 wings! Gonna get reg fries next time coz there was an overload of parmesan chunks on the garlic parm fries. They gave us comp chips\/salsa while we waited for our food. Was not offered thrifty ice cream @ the end
Tacos El Gordo is still better. The flavors don't even compare. Not happy with my asada or Al pastor. Nice ambience though
Upload pix from ur phone\/social media & print them for a buck on a thick Polaroid looking paper. They have some cute and unique frames!
Tried the asada(gr8), Al pastor(gr8), adobada(awesome), puerco verde(awesome) & crunchy tacos(meh, like del taco)! Thumbs up on the house Margarita & dirty south Andy! Friendly service
They skimp on portion sizes here. My fiance and I were still hungry after!
Oreo boba!  Gonna try the caramel macchiato next
They've got sorbet sticks for my lactose intolerant fiancé!
Fresh juices\/veggies, smoothies & booze mixed w\/ juice! Though tasty, it's overpriced. (despicably tasty is good) Reminds me of a jamba juice that serves liquor
They don't test for mthfr or elevated homocysteine levels here for genetic testing.
Located inside Khourys Fine Wine. Suite 110
They have pretty good smoothies here! Limited quest bar flavors & are @ $2.75 a piece (you can get it cheaper elsewhere)
Hot n ready is a joke. We usually have to wait
Beef Noodle soup was really good but they skimped on the meat. Thumbs up on the juicy beef soup dumplings!
Amazing service from Alex!  My son smells gr8, nicely groomed & the facility smells so good.  They really took the time w\/ my dog & can tell they treat the animals well.  Highly recommend
Ridiculously awesome Hip hop music if Franzen is the DJ!! If u avoid the elevators when you're ready to leave,  keep in mind it's 6 flights of stairs!
No self park garage. Park at Flamingo garage or linq lot. There were no signs too,  we drove around for over half an hr trying to figure it out!
Came here on a Friday night. They played awesome Hip hop music and $2 wells. So many flavors for hookah!
